Yes, they look like this:

```js
if (isES5) {
  module.exports = { defineProperty: Object.defineProperty }
}
else {
  module.exports = { defineProperty: myLocalDefineProperty }
}
```

So `es5.defineProperty` has a union type. However, this isn't a regression; it behaves the same way in 3.0. So it must be a code change on bluebird's part.
